    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA354-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu tōḻiyāṟ ceṟippaṟivuṟīi varaivu kaṭāyatu.
            2. maṉaivayiṉ tōḻiyait talaimakaḷ pukaḻntāṟku maṟuttuc colliyatūumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is how marriage was asked for by the confidante, informing of connfinement. 2. It is also what SHE said in the house in refusal in order to praise the confidante.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA354">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>tāṉatu poṟuttal yāvatu kāṉa</l>
<l>lāṭarai yoḻitta nīṭirum peṇṇai</l>
<l>vīḻkā vōlaic cūḻciṟai yātta</l>
<l>kāṉa ṉaṇṇiya vārmaṇaṉ muṉṟi</l>
<l>lelli yaṉṉa viruṇiṟap puṉṉai</l>
<l>nallarai muḻumuta lavvayiṟ ṟoṭutta</l>
<l>tūṅka lampit tūvalañ cērppiṟ</l>
<l>kaṭuveyiṟ kotitta kalviḷai yuppu</l>
<l>neṭuneṟi yoḻukai niraicelap pārppō</l>
<l>raḷampō kākulaṅ kaṭuppak</l>
<l>kauvaiyā kiṉṟa taiyaniṉ ṉaṭpē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>How can one bear that?<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">tāṉ atu poṟuttal yāvatu</term>, literally "oneself bearing that - what?" - what is the rhetoric impact of this question?</note></l>
<l>Slander, o lord, became your intimacy,</l>
<l rend="indent">	like the agitation going through the salt-pan</l>
<l rend="indent2">	of those who see, when they go, the rows of carts on the long path,</l>
<l>	with stony ripe salt boiled by the fierce sunlight</l>
<l rend="indent3">	on the drizzling coast<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">ūvalam</term>: why here the adj. suffix -am? (An adjective does not make it better: "a coast pretty by drizzling"?)</note> with boats hanging,</l>
<l rend="indent2">	linked to the whole base of the good trunks</l>
<l rend="indent2">	of the Puṉṉai trees coloured dark as night</l>
<l rend="indent3">	in the front yards overflowing with sand situated</l>
<l rend="indent3">	by the seashore grove,</l>
<l rend="indent2">	bound to a surrounding fence of sheltering palm-leaves that</l>
<l rend="indent2"> 	descend from the long dark palmyra trees that cast off(?) swaying</l>
<l rend="indent2"> 	trunks in the seashore grove.</l>
      </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
